properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 10:10PM PST until January 28 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow continued. Additional snow accumulations of up to 7
inches.

* WHERE...Olympic mountains and valleys, including Hurricane
Ridge, Amanda Park, and Quinault.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels around 5000 feet tonight will
fall to around 3500 feet Tuesday. Dangerous avalanche conditions
are expected to develop across the Cascades this evening and
very dangerous conditions may develop tonight into Tuesday.
Expect the threat of large and potentially naturally-triggered
avalanches.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY
